# AWS Serverless RAG Platform Implementation Plan

## Objective

Build a production-ready, serverless Retrieval-Augmented Generation platform on AWS that:

- ingests user-uploaded documents in multiple formats
- extracts and normalizes text
- groups and tags documents intelligently
- stores embeddings in Amazon S3 Vectors through Amazon Bedrock Knowledge Bases
- supports both batch and streaming chat APIs
- preserves session history in DynamoDB
- returns exact source citations with every grounded answer
- remains modular so ingestion, retrieval, and chat logic can evolve independently

This plan is written as an execution-ready specification for Claude to implement the project end to end.

