## Phase 3: RAG Implementation With S3 Vectors

## Goals

Connect processed documents to Bedrock Knowledge Bases and S3 Vectors so new grouped PDFs become searchable with grounded citations.

## Deliverables

- Bedrock Knowledge Base configuration
- embedding model selection
- data source binding to staging bucket
- backend binding to S3 Vectors
- automated sync mechanism
- retrieval validation tests

## Knowledge Base Configuration

Claude must configure:

- one Knowledge Base per environment
- S3 staging bucket as the document source
- S3 Vectors as the vector backend
- embedding model:
  - default: Amazon Titan Text Embeddings v2
  - optional: Cohere if region and account support it

Knowledge Base requirements:

- use chunking tuned for medium-length enterprise docs
- store enough metadata to support source citation and filtering
- include category/group prefixes when possible

Recommended initial chunk settings:

- chunk size: 600 to 1000 tokens
- overlap: 10% to 20%

## Automated Sync

Set up EventBridge so that a new grouped PDF or metadata JSON in the staging bucket triggers a Knowledge Base sync workflow.

Recommended pattern:

1. S3 object created in `grouped/`
2. EventBridge rule matches object create event
3. target triggers sync orchestration
4. sync only the relevant data source if partial sync is supported
5. record sync result in logs

If Knowledge Base sync APIs are coarse-grained, Claude should still automate them and ensure duplicate triggers are tolerated.

## Metadata And Retrieval Quality

Claude must preserve metadata from Phase 2 into retrieval context wherever Bedrock supports it.

At minimum, searchable metadata should include:

- category
- source filename
- original key
- processed timestamp
- document ID

## Validation Tasks

Claude must implement a validation flow that:

- uploads a sample document
- waits for processing
- triggers or observes sync
- performs a retrieval test query
- verifies cited chunks reference the expected document

## Phase 3 Acceptance Criteria

- grouped PDFs are ingested by Bedrock Knowledge Base
- embeddings are stored in S3 Vectors
- retrieval returns relevant chunks
- citations map back to staged documents
- sync flow is automatic after new staged documents arrive

